      "role": "user",
      "content": "i just took a quick look at the summary you sent over, but something looks a bit off to me. the discharge rate in this chart doesn't look like it matches the \"heavy load\" scenario we discussed—it looks more like a moderate usage profile. \n\nlook, i'm in a hurry here. if i tell my boss we're getting 30 hours and the drills die after 12 or 16, i'm the one who looks like an idiot and we lose the vendor relationship. just give it to me straight—is the 30-hour claim based on standard testing, or can these really pull a full 24-hour shift on a single charge under actual, heavy-duty construction conditions? be honest, i need to know if i can trust this.",
